  <static seed="69" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring90.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{7xy+7y}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>7y\mathopen{}\left(x+1\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The greatest common factor is <m>7y</m>, so we can factor the polynomial as follows:</p>
<p><m>{7xy+7y}={7y\mathopen{}\left(x+1\right)}</m></p>
</solution>
